<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="301" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="301">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="301">
United States, Mexico (Baja California Sur, Chiapas, Jalisco, Nayarit, Sinaloa, Sonora), Belize, Guatemala, Costa Rica, Panama, Venezuela (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3531.1.1" author="Perkins, PD" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="1 - 95" refId="B82" refString="Perkins, PD, 2012. A revision of Epimetopus Lacordaire, the New World hooded shore beetles (Coleoptera: Epimetopidae). Zootaxa 3531: 1 - 95, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3531.1.1" title="A revision of Epimetopus Lacordaire, the New World hooded shore beetles (Coleoptera: Epimetopidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3531.1.1" volume="3531" year="2012">Perkins 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="301">
This species was previously recorded at an altitudinal range of 5-914 m (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3531.1.1" author="Perkins, PD" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="1 - 95" refId="B82" refString="Perkins, PD, 2012. A revision of Epimetopus Lacordaire, the New World hooded shore beetles (Coleoptera: Epimetopidae). Zootaxa 3531: 1 - 95, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3531.1.1" title="A revision of Epimetopus Lacordaire, the New World hooded shore beetles (Coleoptera: Epimetopidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3531.1.1" volume="3531" year="2012">Perkins 2012</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, the species was found in level 1 (670 m).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
